  {
   "id": "144c9e4d",
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "## Part 4: AGSDR Multi-Objective Fine-Tuning\n\n**Goal:** use AGSDR (adaptive genetic-stochastic delta-rule) to tune population drive strengths so that the first half of neurons approaches 5 Hz and the second half approaches 10 Hz.\n\n**Algorithm view:** AGSDR combines genetic search (population candidates), stochastic exploration (random variation), and score-directed steps (delta rule):\n\n$$J(\\theta) = w_1 \\left( \\hat{r}_1(\\theta) - 5 \\right)^2 + w_2 \\left( \\hat{r}_2(\\theta) - 10 \\right)^2$$\n\n$$\\theta_{g+1} = \\theta_g + \\Delta_{\\mathrm{genetic}} + \\Delta_{\\mathrm{stochastic}} + \\Delta_{\\mathrm{delta}}$$\n\n**Worded equation:** score = weighted mismatch between simulated group-wise firing rates and target group-wise firing rates.\n\n**Scope:** This is a computational scaffold optimization. The tuned drive scales are relative to the baseline Izhikevich model; no biological calibration, no empirical validation.",
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "id": "1f732af9",
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "source": "# Part 4: AGSDR Multi-Objective Fine-Tuning\n# Tune drive strengths for two population halves toward different rate targets: 5 Hz / 10 Hz.\n\n# Baseline: simulate to establish initial group-wise rates\nprint(\"Baseline simulation (group-wise rates):\")\nsig_baseline = jtfne.simulate(model_column, duration_ms=DURATION_MS, dt_ms=DT_MS, seed=SEED + 2)\nspikes_baseline = np.asarray(sig_baseline.spikes)\nn_neurons = spikes_baseline.shape[1]\nn_half = n_neurons // 2\n\nbaseline_rates = spikes_baseline.mean(axis=0) * 1000.0 / DT_MS\nbaseline_group_a = baseline_rates[:n_half].mean()\nbaseline_group_b = baseline_rates[n_half:].mean()\n\nprint(f\"  Group A (neurons 0–{n_half-1}): {baseline_group_a:.2f} Hz (target: 5 Hz)\")\nprint(f\"  Group B (neurons {n_half}–{n_neurons-1}): {baseline_group_b:.2f} Hz (target: 10 Hz)\")\n\n# Define optimization targets\ntargets_hz = {\"group_a\": 5.0, \"group_b\": 10.0}\n\n# Helper function: compute group-wise rates\ndef group_rates_hz(spikes: np.ndarray, dt_ms: float) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Return firing rates for first and second halves of a population.\"\"\"\n    spikes = np.asarray(spikes)\n    n_neurons = spikes.shape[1]\n    n_half = n_neurons // 2\n    return {\n        \"group_a\": population_rate_hz(spikes[:, :n_half], dt_ms),\n        \"group_b\": population_rate_hz(spikes[:, n_half:], dt_ms),\n    }\n\n# Helper function: compute multi-objective score\ndef multi_objective_score(rates: dict, targets: dict) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Squared relative error for group A (5 Hz) and group B (10 Hz).\"\"\"\n    error_a = ((rates[\"group_a\"] - targets[\"group_a\"]) / targets[\"group_a\"]) ** 2\n    error_b = ((rates[\"group_b\"] - targets[\"group_b\"]) / targets[\"group_b\"]) ** 2\n    return float(error_a + error_b)\n\n# Helper function: create model with modified drive scales\ndef model_with_drive_scales(base_model, drive_scale_a: float, drive_scale_b: float):\n    \"\"\"Return model where first/second population halves receive different drive scales.\"\"\"\n    emitter = base_model.params[\"emitter\"]\n    base_drive = np.asarray(emitter.drive, dtype=float).reshape(-1)\n    n_units = base_drive.shape[0]\n    split = n_units // 2\n\n    drive_scale = np.ones(n_units, dtype=float)\n    drive_scale[:split] = float(drive_scale_a)\n    drive_scale[split:] = float(drive_scale_b)\n    drive_per_neuron = base_drive * drive_scale\n\n    return base_model.with_emitter_parameters(drive_per_neuron=drive_per_neuron)\n\n# AGSDR parameters\nagsdr_alpha = 0.65\nagsdr_exploration = 0.18\nagsdr_deselect_factor = 2.0\nn_generations = 8\nn_population = 6\nopt_duration_ms = 1000.0\nopt_seed = SEED + 3\ndrive_scale_bounds = np.array([[0.35, 2.25], [0.35, 2.25]], dtype=float)\n\n# Initialize AGSDR state\nrng = np.random.default_rng(opt_seed)\ntheta_center = np.array([1.0, 1.0], dtype=float)  # initial center (balanced)\nbest_record = None\ngeneration_history = []\n\nprint(f\"\\nRunning AGSDR multi-objective tuning ({n_generations} generations × {n_population} candidates)...\")\nprint(f\"{'Gen':<4} {'Best Score':<12} {'Group A (Hz)':<14} {'Group B (Hz)':<14} {'Scales (A, B)':<20}\")\nprint(\"─\" * 70)\n\nfor generation in range(n_generations):\n    generation_candidates = []\n    generation_records = []\n\n    # Genetic candidates: preserve center and add stochastic variations\n    for candidate_idx in range(n_population):\n        if candidate_idx == 0:\n            # First candidate: use current center\n            proposal = theta_center.copy()\n        else:\n            # Remaining candidates: add stochastic exploration\n            stochastic_step = rng.normal(loc=0.0, scale=agsdr_exploration, size=2)\n            proposal = theta_center + stochastic_step\n\n        # Clip to bounds\n        proposal = np.clip(proposal, drive_scale_bounds[:, 0], drive_scale_bounds[:, 1])\n        generation_candidates.append(proposal)\n\n        # Evaluate candidate\n        candidate_model = model_with_drive_scales(model_column, float(proposal[0]), float(proposal[1]))\n        candidate_signals = jtfne.simulate(\n            candidate_model,\n            duration_ms=opt_duration_ms,\n            dt_ms=DT_MS,\n            seed=opt_seed + generation * 100 + candidate_idx,\n        )\n        candidate_spikes = np.asarray(candidate_signals.spikes)\n        rates = group_rates_hz(candidate_spikes, DT_MS)\n        score = multi_objective_score(rates, targets_hz)\n\n        record = {\n            \"generation\": int(generation),\n            \"candidate\": int(candidate_idx),\n            \"drive_scale_a\": float(proposal[0]),\n            \"drive_scale_b\": float(proposal[1]),\n            \"rate_group_a_hz\": float(rates[\"group_a\"]),\n            \"rate_group_b_hz\": float(rates[\"group_b\"]),\n            \"score\": float(score),\n        }\n        generation_records.append(record)\n\n        if best_record is None or score < best_record[\"score\"]:\n            best_record = dict(record)\n\n    # Find best in generation and update center via delta step\n    generation_best = min(generation_records, key=lambda r: r[\"score\"])\n    generation_best_theta = np.array([\n        generation_best[\"drive_scale_a\"],\n        generation_best[\"drive_scale_b\"],\n    ], dtype=float)\n\n    # Delta step: move center toward best candidate\n    delta = generation_best_theta - theta_center\n    theta_center = theta_center + agsdr_alpha * delta\n    theta_center = np.clip(theta_center, drive_scale_bounds[:, 0], drive_scale_bounds[:, 1])\n\n    generation_history.append({\n        \"generation\": int(generation),\n        \"best_score\": float(best_record[\"score\"]),\n        \"best_rates\": {\n            \"group_a\": float(best_record[\"rate_group_a_hz\"]),\n            \"group_b\": float(best_record[\"rate_group_b_hz\"]),\n        },\n        \"best_scales\": {\n            \"group_a\": float(best_record[\"drive_scale_a\"]),\n            \"group_b\": float(best_record[\"drive_scale_b\"]),\n        },\n        \"candidates\": generation_records,\n    })\n\n    print(f\"{generation:<4} {best_record['score']:<12.4f} {best_record['rate_group_a_hz']:<14.2f} {best_record['rate_group_b_hz']:<14.2f} ({best_record['drive_scale_a']:.3f}, {best_record['drive_scale_b']:.3f})\")\n\nprint(\"─\" * 70)\nprint(f\"✓ AGSDR completed after {n_generations} generations ({n_generations * n_population} total evaluations)\")\n\n# Create tuned model with best parameters\nif best_record is not None:\n    best_scales = np.array([\n        best_record[\"drive_scale_a\"],\n        best_record[\"drive_scale_b\"],\n    ], dtype=float)\n    model_tuned = model_with_drive_scales(model_column, float(best_scales[0]), float(best_scales[1]))\nelse:\n    best_scales = np.array([np.nan, np.nan], dtype=float)\n    model_tuned = model_column\n\n# Evaluate tuned model with full-duration simulation\nprint(\"\\nFinal validation (full 5000 ms simulation):\")\nsig_tuned = jtfne.simulate(model_tuned, duration_ms=DURATION_MS, dt_ms=DT_MS, seed=SEED + 4)\nspikes_tuned = np.asarray(sig_tuned.spikes)\n\ntuned_rates = group_rates_hz(spikes_tuned, DT_MS)\ntuned_group_a = tuned_rates[\"group_a\"]\ntuned_group_b = tuned_rates[\"group_b\"]\n\nerror_a_baseline = abs(baseline_group_a - targets_hz[\"group_a\"])\nerror_a_tuned = abs(tuned_group_a - targets_hz[\"group_a\"])\nerror_b_baseline = abs(baseline_group_b - targets_hz[\"group_b\"])\nerror_b_tuned = abs(tuned_group_b - targets_hz[\"group_b\"])\n\nprint(f\"  Group A: {baseline_group_a:.2f} Hz → {tuned_group_a:.2f} Hz (target: {targets_hz['group_a']:.1f} Hz)\")\nprint(f\"    Error: {error_a_baseline:.2f} Hz → {error_a_tuned:.2f} Hz\")\nprint(f\"  Group B: {baseline_group_b:.2f} Hz → {tuned_group_b:.2f} Hz (target: {targets_hz['group_b']:.1f} Hz)\")\nprint(f\"    Error: {error_b_baseline:.2f} Hz → {error_b_tuned:.2f} Hz\")\n\n# Public-facing tuning report\ntuning_report = {\n    \"tuning_status\": \"agsdr_multi_objective_completed\",\n    \"tuning_method\": \"genetic_stochastic_delta_rule\",\n    \"generations\": int(n_generations),\n    \"population_per_generation\": int(n_population),\n    \"total_evaluations\": int(n_generations * n_population),\n    \"parameters_tuned\": [\"drive_scale_group_a\", \"drive_scale_group_b\"],\n    \"parameter_bounds\": {\n        \"drive_scale_group_a\": list(drive_scale_bounds[0]),\n        \"drive_scale_group_b\": list(drive_scale_bounds[1]),\n    },\n    \"targets_hz\": targets_hz,\n    \"final_rates_hz\": {\n        \"group_a\": round(tuned_group_a, 2),\n        \"group_b\": round(tuned_group_b, 2),\n    },\n    \"best_drive_scales\": {\n        \"group_a\": round(float(best_scales[0]), 4),\n        \"group_b\": round(float(best_scales[1]), 4),\n    },\n    \"initial_score\": round(multi_objective_score(group_rates_hz(spikes_baseline, DT_MS), targets_hz), 4),\n    \"final_best_score\": round(float(best_record[\"score\"]), 4) if best_record else np.nan,\n    \"scope_status\": \"computational_scaffold\",\n    \"readout_status\": \"proxy_scale\",\n}\n\njson.dumps(tuning_report, allow_nan=False)\nprint(\"\\nTuning report (JSON-safe):\")\nprint(json.dumps(tuning_report, indent=2))\n\n# Visualize AGSDR progress and final rates\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 4))\n\n# Left: best-score trajectory\nbest_scores = [h[\"best_score\"] for h in generation_history]\naxes[0].plot(np.arange(len(best_scores)), best_scores, marker=\"o\", lw=2, markersize=6)\naxes[0].set_xlabel(\"Generation\")\naxes[0].set_ylabel(\"Best objective score\")\naxes[0].set_title(\"Figure 4a — AGSDR Multi-Objective Score Progress\")\naxes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n# Right: final group-wise rates vs. targets\ngroups = [\"Group A\\n(target 5 Hz)\", \"Group B\\n(target 10 Hz)\"]\nbaseline_vals = [baseline_group_a, baseline_group_b]\ntuned_vals = [tuned_group_a, tuned_group_b]\ntarget_vals = [targets_hz[\"group_a\"], targets_hz[\"group_b\"]]\n\nx = np.arange(len(groups))\nwidth = 0.25\n\naxes[1].bar(x - width, baseline_vals, width, label=\"Baseline\", alpha=0.8)\naxes[1].bar(x, tuned_vals, width, label=\"Tuned\", alpha=0.8)\naxes[1].scatter(x, target_vals, marker=\"*\", s=300, color=\"red\", label=\"Target\", zorder=5)\n\naxes[1].set_ylabel(\"Firing rate (Hz)\")\naxes[1].set_title(\"Figure 4b — Group-Wise Rate Targets and Achieved Rates\")\naxes[1].set_xticks(x)\naxes[1].set_xticklabels(groups)\naxes[1].legend(frameon=False)\naxes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis=\"y\")\n\nfig.tight_layout()\nsave_png(fig, \"08_agsdr_multi_objective_progress\")",
   "outputs": []
  },
